{"data":[{"name":"107:1","price":"1. Have you seen him who denies the Recompense?","arabic":"أَرَءَيۡتَ ٱلَّذِي يُكَذِّبُ بِٱلدِّينِ","category":["107 (Al-Ma'un)","Al-Ma'un","Surah Al-Ma'un"],"ayahNumber":6198,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"ara-ayta alladhī yukadhibu bil-dīni ","translations":["Have you seen","the one who","denies","the Judgment","(1)"],"transliterationArr":["ara-ayta","alladhī","yukadhibu","bil-dīni",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1010],[2,1010,1670],[3,1670,2990],[4,2990,6185]]}},{"name":"107:2","price":" 2. That is he who repulses the orphan (harshly),[1]","arabic":"فَذَٰلِكَ ٱلَّذِي يَدُعُّ ٱلۡيَتِيمَ","category":["107 (Al-Ma'un)","Al-Ma'un","Surah Al-Ma'un"],"ayahNumber":6199,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"(V.107:2) Narrated Sahl bin Sa‘d رضي الله عنهما : The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم said, \"I and the person who looks after an orphan and provides for him, will be in Paradise like this,\" putting his index and middle fingers together. (Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol.8, Hadith No.34).","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"fadhālika alladhī yaduʿʿu al-yatīma ","translations":["Then that","(is) the one who","repulses","the orphan","(2)"],"transliterationArr":["fadhālika","alladhī","yaduʿʿu","al-yatīma",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1150],[2,1150,2000],[3,2000,2770],[4,2770,6435]]}},{"name":"107:3","price":" 3. And urges not on the feeding of Al-Miskîn (the poor),[2]","arabic":"وَلَا يَحُضُّ عَلَىٰ طَعَامِ ٱلۡمِسۡكِينِ","category":["107 (Al-Ma'un)","Al-Ma'un","Surah Al-Ma'un"],"ayahNumber":6200,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"(V.107:3) Narrated Abû Hurairah رضي الله عنه: The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم said, \"The one who looks after a widow or a poor person is like a Mujâhid (fighter) who fights for Allâh’s Cause, or like him who performs prayers all the night and fasts all the day.\" (Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol.7, Hadith No.265).","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"walā yaḥuḍḍu ʿalā ṭaʿāmi al-mis'kīni ","translations":["And (does) n